<br>
B) In general, Data concerning RL activities of guild members should not be considered to be public information.  If it were, they'd post in the public forum about it.  This is for privacy and security (the comfort kind *and* the safety kind).<br>
<br>
C) There are lots of reasons at the moment why applications are being temporarily held up.  I would like to assure everyone that we're not just sitting here twiddling our thumbs and laughing cruelly at all the nice folk who want to join us.  I myself have 2 people I really really would like to see accepted into the Guild, like yesterday.  None of this is going to happen overnight, and I hope that we end up being worth the wait.<br>
<br>
I plead for everyones' patience and understanding.  And I apologize if I offend anyone by this post.  Sometimes I'm a stick in the mud.<br>
<br>
Morgen, Lorekeeper <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bridh>Bridh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sister</span><br>  Posts: 356<br> <font color=#660000>(2/10/02 3:33:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=262.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Initiates, applications, etc</span><hr size=1> Mebbe an Elder could drop in a lil note so folks know it's on hold. That way we all know what's going on.<br>
